Cell.Text: Then... it's over and my death wasn't in vain. | I owe you a great deal, Nightingale.

Cell.Text: [S] You've done the Guild a great deed. And although they may not show it, I'm certain they appreciate your sacrifices. | My only regret is that you had to undertake this task alone.

Node.Caption: TG09GallusIntroBranchTopic01c: I did this to honor the Guild.

Cell.Text: Nothing would bring me more pride than to return the Key, but I'm afraid it's impossible. | From the moment I arrived here, I've felt myself... well... dying.

Node.Caption: TG09GallusFinalIntroBranchTopic: Then take the Key and right all the wrongs.

Cell.Text: The Sepulcher isn't merely a temple or a vault to house the Key. Within these walls is the Ebonmere... a conduit to Nocturnal's realm of Evergloam. | When Mercer stole the Key, that conduit closed, severely limiting our ties to her.

[S] I'm afraid so. I'm weakening, and I can feel myself slipping away. The years without restoration of my power have taken their toll. | Whatever damage has been caused can only be corrected by following the Pilgrim's Path to the Ebonmere and replacing the Key.

Node.Caption: TG09GallusFinalIntroBranchTopic03: Then I'll have to proceed alone.

Cell.Text: [S] I don't recognize you, but I sense that you're one of us. Who are you?
The last of the Nightingale Sentinels, I'm afraid. I've defended the Sepulcher alone for what seems like an eternity.

Node.Caption: TG09PlayerInitialReactionBranchTopic01: I'd ask the same question of you.

Cell.Text: We were betrayed by one of our own kind. In fact, I'm to blame for what's happened here.

Node.Caption: TG09PlayerInitialReactionBranchTopic02: The last? What happened to the rest?

Cell.Text: I was blinded. Blinded by dark treachery masquerading as friendship. | Perhaps if I had been more vigilant, then Mercer Frey wouldn't have lured me to my fate and stolen the Skeleton Key.
[S] I haven't heard that name in a long time. | How do you know of me?
Karliah... she's still alive? | I feared she'd befallen the same fate, ending up a victim of Mercer's betrayal.
